  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">New Life, Northern Shan Drug Prevention (NSDP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Raise awareness of the problems drug abuse cause. Prevention activities for those that have never used drugs.  Rehabilitation activities for drug users. 
The recreational and social activities for the youth include sports and a video parlor.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The New Life Program is a community-based intervention to reduce the
number of youths who abuse drugs for the first time and to prevent or reduce occasional abuse among both adults and youths in 30 villages. The intervention includes three components: 1) a community-based, community-driven development of a drug prevention plan, including a focus on raising awareness of the danger of the occasional abuse of drugs; 2) a life-skills
program for high risk youths in the villages where World Concern directly implements the program; and 3) a capacity-building intervention for local partners who will pursue the first component in additional villages.</narrative>
  </description>
